entries.title: Former England rugby player and I'm a Celebrity star Mike Tindall charges £20,000 for clay-shooting
entries.description: Former England rugby star Mike Tindall, 44, married to King Charles's niece Zara, is inviting wealthy fans to a farm in the Cotswolds for clay-shooting day packages at a cost of £20,000.

entries.title: Relief for 1.7million Britons suffering urinary tract infections
entries.description: Experts have hailed gepotidacin as a huge step forward in the fight against antibiotic resistance, because the bugs have not had a chance to become resistant to its attacks.

entries.title: Army spied on lockdown critics: Sceptics, including Peter Hitchens, suspected they being watched
entries.description: Military operatives in the UK's 'information warfare' brigade were part of a operation that targeted politicians and high-profile journalists who raised doubts about the official pandemic response.

entries.title: Kaivon Washington is now accused of raping a 12-year-old girl when he was 15 in 2020
entries.description: One of the suspects in the rape of LSU sophomore Madison Brooks is now facing a separate rape charge relating to an attack on a 12-year-old girl in 2020.

entries.title: Sydney Airport control tower incident sparks evacuations and flight delays
entries.description: Sydney Airport has been thrown into chaos after an incident in the control tower sparking  evacuations and delays to flights.

entries.title: King Charles WANTS Harry and Meghan to attend his Coronation
entries.description: The King has asked the Archbishop of Canterbury to broker a deal to allow Harry to attend his Coronation - but has met resistance from William, The Mail on Sunday can reveal.

entries.title: Nadhim Zahawi is on the brink as rivals 'audition' for his job as Tory Chairman
entries.description: The Mail on Sunday was told that three Cabinet Ministers appeared to be 'auditioning' for the role at last week's Cabinet away-day at Chequers.

entries.title: IAN BIRRELL: UN experts say lab leak was the 'most likely' cause of Covid-19

entries.title: You reddit here first! William and Harry's frog wellies hop back into fashion... for adults
entries.description: With their googly eyes and wide red mouths, novelty frog wellies became essential footwear for any well-dressed child of the 1980s - thanks to toddler Princes William and Harry raising their profile.

entries.title: There has been a suppression of the truth, secrecy and cover-ups over origin of Covid-19 in China

entries.title: Britain's Got Talent alsatian's police handler has dogs taken away 'in illicit breeding inquiry'
entries.description: Police dog handler PC David Wardell, from Hertfordshire, who found fame on Britain's Got Talent with his alsatian Finn, is being investigated amid 'welfare' concerns for dogs in his care.

entries.title: Could it be YOU? Two National Lottery ticketholders both win £6MILLION
entries.description: Two lucky ticketholders have each won £6million in Saturday's National Lottery draw. The winners bagged half of the £12million Lotto 'Must Be Won' jackpot by matching all six main numbers.

entries.title: How vapes threaten to undo Australia's war on smoking with students turning to e-cigarettes

entries.title: Australian capital cities where houses were still affordable in 2020 for average income earner
entries.description: An Australian earning an average, full-time salary in November 2020 could still buy a house in Brisbane, Adelaide or Hobart without being in mortgage stress - but not anymore. The Reserve Bank is to blame.

entries.title: Marie Kondo says she's 'kind of given up' on tidying up after having three kids
entries.description: She and her husband now plan family time into their days and find small activities that spark joy, including burning incense and drinking a cup of tea.

entries.title: Australian Mr Universe Calum von Moger cuts up kangaroo with a chainsaw
entries.description: Troubled bodybuilder Calum von Moger mowed down the kangaroo in his Ford Ranger ute and cut up its body at his home in Geelong, feeding the tail to his dog and keeping the head 'as a memento'.

entries.title: AP is mocked on Twitter after telling journalists to avoid using 'dehumanising' phrase 'the French'
entries.description: AP said it 'did not intend to offend' French citizens and reiterated that using 'the' terms when describing people can 'sound dehumanizing' and 'imply a monolith.'

entries.title: Hundreds of Extinction Rebellion protesters wave banners outside The Hague saying it is 'a dead end'
entries.description: In their latest climate change stunt, the protestors waved coloured flags adorned with the Extinction Rebellion symbol as they gathered on the A12.

entries.title: Ex-Tory chairman Sir Jake Berry opens up about depression struggles sparked by brother's death
entries.description: Former Conservative Party chairman Sir Jake Berry (pictured) has opened up about his depression and struggles with his mental health which were sparked after the death of his brother.

entries.title: Cop charged with Tyre Nichols's murder was head of Mississippi frat that paddled man's testicles
entries.description: Tadarrius Bean, 24, who was fired over his role in Tyre Nichols' brutal beating, served as the head of the Omega Psi Phi's Eta Zeta chapter at the University of Mississippi.

entries.title: Veteran librarian 'regrets every day' moving to Michigan town at the center of book banning wars
entries.description: A librarian in Michigan has seen her place of work become a lightening rod for a group of radical conservatives seeking to ban books they believe promote pornography or LGBTQ causes.

entries.title: Jamaican police charge man for murdering British brother while visiting for his mother's funeral
entries.description: Michael Brown, from Waterford in Hertfordshire, was shot dead in Mike Town earlier this month. It is reported that his brother Lemone Brown has been arrested and charged with murder.

entries.title: Fears grow for missing 32-year-old man last seen seven days ago
entries.description: Nathan Cole, 32, from Notting Hill was last in contact with his family at 9.33pm on 21 January in Wandsworth. He told them that he was going to a gig in Camden, north London.

entries.title: TJ Holmes and Amy Robach spotted kissing and embracing after GMA departure news breaks

entries.title: STEVE HILTON: Adam Schiff is one of democracy's greatest threats

entries.title: Las Vegas locals warn Londoners new concert venue MSG Sphere like 'sun on Earth' with 36m lights

entries.title: Pope Francis says people who criminalise homosexual acts are 'wrong'
entries.description: The letter comes after the Pope said earlier this week that homosexuality is 'not a crime' but that 'it's a sin' . It was written to clarify his comments in the interview with the Associated Press.

entries.title: Trump denounces claims he's 'not campaigning' in first high-profile 2024 speech
entries.description: Trump's first high-profile 2024 campaign event had him defending against claims he has been slow to start his campaign - and saying every day feels like April Fools Day with Biden in the US.

entries.title: Activist at California reparations meeting slams $223K proposed payments as 'not enough'
entries.description: Activist Reverend Tony Pierce blasted the $223,000 payments proposed for black residents in California - yelling almost a quarter of a million dollars for each person is 'not enough'.

entries.title: Sister says law must change after British boyfriend lured Canadian teenager to UK and murdered her
entries.description: Ashley Wadsworth (pictured), from Canada was strangled and stabbed more than 90 times in a vicious attack by her 23-year-old boyfriend Jack Sepple , a year ago this week.

entries.description: Among those to raise concerns this week was Ashlyn DeLong, who has claimed staffers at the Walterboro Wildlife Center did not notify her about the arrangement ahead of her wedding to fiancé Josh.

entries.title: Experts solve mystery of Royal Society's baffling medieval manuscript - but can YOU crack the code?
entries.description: For centuries a medieval almanac has baffled historians with its confusing array of liturgical and astronomical calendars, depictions of monthly activities and figures of the zodiac.

entries.title: Police seize arsenal of samurai swords, daggers and hand axes in raid on property in Putney
entries.description: Wandsworth Police descended on the property in Putney yesterday and recovered a huge array of weapons, totalling 15 types of swords following a warrant to search the property.

entries.description: Peter Galea and his friend Joseph McKinnon were fishing in a motor boat 400 metres off Portland in Victoria's south-west when the terrifying great white shark struck.

entries.description: Westminster City Council said it is temporarily shutting down the second of its UriLift toilets, on Villiers Street, as a 'precautionary measure'.
